		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000602E"
		x: 6.0d
		y: -3.0d
		dependencies: ["0000000000006008"]
		title: "Seared Alloys"
		icon: {id: "minecraft:copper_ingot", Count: 1b}
		description: ["The Smeltery doesn't just melt iron. Fill it with copper and tin — tin ore spawns below y=0 alongside copper — and they alloy into Bronze. Bronze tool parts are stronger than iron and carry material traits that iron lacks.", "Cast new heads from liquid bronze and rebuild your tool kit from the Smeltery, not the Part Builder."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000602F"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Smelt copper and tin into bronze in the Tinkers Smeltery"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "0000000000006030"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:iron_ingot", Count: 8b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000006031"
		x: 8.0d
		y: -3.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000602E"]
		title: "The Modifier"
		icon: {id: "tconstruct:pickaxe", Count: 1b}
		description: ["At use milestones, your Tinkers tool earns a Modifier Slot. Open the Tinker's Anvil and slot in a material to activate it: Redstone speeds up mining, Lapis generates bonus experience, a Netherite Scrap adds a large raw stat jump. Three of the same modifier in one slot stacks the effect.", "The tool remembers every modifier you've applied. Plan your loadout before you fill the slots."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "0000000000006032"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Apply a modifier to any Tinkers Construct tool"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "0000000000006033"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:lapis_lazuli", Count: 16b}
		}, {
			id: "0000000000006034"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:redstone", Count: 16b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000006035"
		x: 10.0d
		y: -1.0d
		dependencies: ["0000000000006017"]
		title: "The Alloy Maker"
		icon: {id: "silentgear:alloy_maker", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Silent Gear's Alloy Maker blends ingots into materials that vanilla crafting can't produce — Crimson Iron, Tyrian Steel, and others. These alloys are the backbone of mid-tier Silent Gear parts. It runs like a furnace: feed in materials, wait for the output, repeat.", "The alloy tier you can make now determines the part tier you can build next."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "0000000000006036"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "silentgear:alloy_maker", Count: 1b}
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "0000000000006037"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "silentgear:blueprint_package", Count: 1b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000006038"
		x: 12.0d
		y: -1.0d
		dependencies: ["0000000000006035"]
		title: "Harvesting in Silence"
		icon: {id: "silentgear:pickaxe", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Craft a Silent Gear pickaxe using alloy-based parts from the Alloy Maker. Silent Gear tools can be fully disassembled and rebuilt at any time — swap a worn tip without losing the grip or rod. They complement Tinkers tools: use Tinkers for the build you've committed to, Silent Gear for the one you're still testing.", "Weapon crafting in this pack is handled by Spartan Weaponry and Iron's Spells. Silent Gear and Tinkers are for harvest tools only."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "0000000000006039"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "silentgear:pickaxe", Count: 1b}
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000603A"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:iron_ingot", Count: 8b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000603B"
		x: 12.0d
		y: 0.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000601A"]
		title: "From the Field"
		icon: {id: "farmersdelight:cooking_pot", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Farmers Delight rewrites early food. The Cutting Board and Knife prep ingredients. The Cooking Pot combines them into real meals — meals that grant Nourished, Hearty, or other lasting buffs that stack on top of your combat stats.", "A proper meal is a better combat upgrade than most iron armor. Build a Cooking Pot and plant the crops you need to keep it running."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000603C"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "farmersdelight:cooking_pot", Count: 1b}
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000000603D"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:apple", Count: 8b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000000603E"
		x: 14.0d
		y: 0.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000603B"]
		title: "Well Fed, Well Armed"
		icon: {id: "farmersdelight:chicken_soup", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Cook something real. A five-ingredient meal from the Cooking Pot grants Nourished — which extends how long your saturation lasts — and Hearty, which generates passive health regeneration. Check JEI under Farmers Delight for a recipe that matches what you've grown.", "The buff duration scales with meal complexity. Don't settle for a two-ingredient soup when you can grow the crops for a full stew."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000000603F"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Cook and eat a proper Farmers Delight meal from the Cooking Pot"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "0000000000006040"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "minecraft:golden_apple", Count: 1b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000006041"
		x: 16.0d
		y: 0.0d
		dependencies: ["000000000000603E"]
		title: "Steel Resolve"
		icon: {id: "gtceu:steel_ingot", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Steel is the gate between iron and everything that comes after. Make it in Thermal Foundation's Induction Smelter — iron ingots pressed with Pulverized Coal — or in GregTech's Blast Furnace once you have power. Either path produces the same steel ingot, accepted by the same recipes.", "The chapter is named after this. Don't skip it. Every machine frame in the next ten hours of play runs on steel."]
		tasks: [{
